<plot>Artists can impact strangers so deeply that they feel they've lost a personal friend when they die. On New Year's Day, little-know musician, Bryan Harvey made national news. The frontman of the 80's rock-duo House Of Freaks was brutally murdered along with his family in their home.  To most of the world this was simply a sensational headline, but for those who treasured Harvey's music, a part of themselves was extinguished.  </plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?117571</url></doc>
